Hiring Me

Kick-Starting Your Project

The scope of work, delivery dates and cost estimate for your project will be defined in writing to aid project planning. I will work with you to establish these items and ensure we are both clear about how your project will be developed.

Communicating Progress

1. Items that were completed

2. Items that I need from you

3. Items that I will be working on next

Keeping Your Website Secure

Copies of all account access credentials that you send me will be stored in an encrypted database (1Password) on my development laptop. The original message containing the credentials will then be deleted to minimize the risk of your website being compromised.

Delivering Quality Code

My top priority is to ease code maintenance and future updates. All code that I produce for you will include clear comments, readable control structures and relevant function names.

Adopting New Languages & Tools

I am always learning new programming skills and can usually pick up a language's fundamentals over a weekend. If there is a tool or API that is critical to your project, I will be happy to get up to speed with its use.

Proofreading Content

As a former English tutor, I can easily correct grammar and awkward wording in written content before it goes live on your website. In order to minimize delays, I will inform you if the content you provide me requires extensive editing.

Optimizing Images

The dimensions of photos and other design assets that you provide me will be tailored to the target display (mobile and/or desktop). Also, the file size of images will be minimized to speed up page load times. Outside of light photo editing, I do not provide graphic design services.

MOBILEIZE The Drive to Purchase Platform [Integrated with Facebook, Twitter, NFC etc.] Patent Pending.

Mobileize connects advertising to purchase locations. We are an innovative cloud based mobile marketing platform that allows brands and retailers to influence purchase behaviour by connecting any communication (on or off-line) to a physical location using any device with an html5 browser (smartphone, tablet, laptop, PC).

Please experience the platform for yourself on your mobile http://fullers.mobileize.co.uk/?find

Please see link to our a short Sales Presentation deck to provide an insight into our product proposition and how we are engaging with major retailers, brands and media owners [e.g. Facebook / Twitter] -

http://www.mobileize.co.uk/uploads/5/3/0/0/5300468/mobileize_drive_to_purchase_overview.pdf.

Our technology has been running flawlessly for 1 year. We have secured 2 clients since filing our patent on 6th June 2013. [Fullers Pubs 400 locations & National Trust 600 locations]. Our platform works globally and we have significant interest from many of the worlds biggest brands including Facebook, Twitter, Coke, McDonalds, Kraft, Cadbury, Tesco, Chrysler.

The market problem

Advertising cant show consumers where they can purchase product, thus creating a barrier in the typical sales funnel or path to purchase. Our vision is to complete the path to purchase by directly linking consumers to the nearest place to purchase in advertising or communications, enabling brands and retailers to interact with consumers when they are at their most receptive. Almost all of the growth in the global advertising market in the next four years will come from mobile related spend. Within the mobile category itself, location based services will be both the largest and the fastest growing, creating a Total Addressable Market of approximately 5 billion USD by 2016 (2 billion USD in 2014). Source: ZenithOptimedia / Berg Insight.

Our solution

Our mobile marketing platform allows any piece of marketing communication to show consumers where they can purchase the advertised product. This is a disruptive approach to advertising, which gives users of the Mobileize platform the following advantages: - we respond to a stated consumer need immediately when engaged within a campaign; - we provide an audience at scale that has expressed an interest to purchase or interact. Scale because it works on any device and within most advertising mediums, including social media, web site, email, press, outdoor and TV (using bar codes, short codes and NFC].

Our Mass Publishing System also enables our clients to target marketing offers and content at consumers on a store by store basis. We provide location and media channel analytics that allows our clients to improve their marketing activity over time.

Our business model

Mobileize derives its revenue from 12 month rolling service contracts with customers. Contracts include a one off set up cost, a monthly charge per location (between 1 and 5) and a campaign management fee based on the number of interactions with a campaign. Average client revenues of 45-85k are expected to increase year-on-year as the platform develops and its usage increases. Contracts have been modelled based on a single install per customer per country.

Competitors

We have identified two key areas that create an unfair advantage over location-based competitors such as Google Places, Foursquare and NearMe. Firstly the Mobileize platform runs in the Cloud so it works on any mobile device and can connect to any communication. We are not restricted to just connecting to advertising that is delivered digitally or on mobile devices. Mobileize works equally well in outdoor or in press advertising and even works on moving buses or trains and on underground transport where Internet is available. Secondly, we have a fast mass publishing system, where individual store information and content can be changed on an hourly basis across thousands of stores.

The Management Team

Gray Sycamore, CTO & Co-Founder was formerly Leo Burnett Group Digital Director and developed the Mobileize technical platform over the last 2 years. Chris Nicholls, CSO & Co-Founder was formerly Worldwide Managing Director International clients at TBWA /TEQUILA Worldwide in New York. Paul Kingsley, CFO has held a number of senior positions within digital businesses including CEO of Oyster Partners (now LBi/Digitas) and has significant experience working with start-up organisations. Members of Advisory Board - Matt Atkinson Chief Marketing Officer Tesco PLC & Jason Kuperman Vice President - Digital, Asia Pacific, India, Middle East and Africa at Omnicom Group.

What we are looking for

Mobileize is a UK registered company (GSCN Limited t/a as Mobileize) and is seeking to secure $1.6M in order to develop the business over the next 12 months in the following specific areas: General working capital; Developing our technology roadmap; We will also develop new business opportunities in international markets initially in North America from Q2 2014. The Management team are looking to achieve revenues in excess of USD 50million by Year 5, equivalent to 1% of the global addressable market.

ROIgeeks Services

Landing page optimization (LPO) and landing page design Conversion rate optimization (CRO)
ROIgeeks help businesses improve their landing pages and websites and generate more revenue without having to spend additional budget on traffic acquisition. The company helps its clients optimize the profitability of their websites. This is achieved by

Eliminating guess work in landing page design
Providing better experience to visitors
Continuous testing and optimization
Optimization Methodology
ROIgeeks optimization process is a multi stage approach, consisting of three major stages, each with multiple steps:

Stage 1. Understand clients business (website, target market and competitors)

Stage 2. Analyze web analytics data for in depth understanding of website users

Stage 3. Design proposals, setting up a/b/n or multivariate tests

Once our team will understand your business goals, the conversion optimization specialists will design and run A/B and multivariate tests using Googles WebSite Optimizer. Test hypothesis are based on web analytics data analysis (using Google Analytics) and other third party tools used to gain insights into your visitors behavior. Web analytics findings, combined with our experience gained over the years are guaranteed to deliver solid results.

Guaranteed Results
We are confident about the results we deliver. Hence our landing page optimization service is backed up by our Results or Money Back Guarantee. That means, if we dont improve your landing page conversion rate by at least 10%, well give your money back. Or, well test until we do.

Working with ROIgeeks
LPO and CRO is a strategic commitment and is critical to scaling a successful online business. When you work with ROIgeeks, you are buying into a philosophy and vision similar to what the big websites use: constantly iterating success as your entire site is analyzed for improved conversion rates. As conversion rates are increasing, not only do your sales go up, but also the profitability of all of your campaigns increases, enabling you to outpace competitors

CAG answers questions and assists consumers in resolving complaints against national banks. The focus of the OCC's review of consumer complaints against national banks is to determine whether the bank's actions are consistent with banking statutes, regulations or any policies that are applicable to nationally chartered banking institutions. The OCC will act on complaints and inquiries that are submitted in writing and signed by the account holder. The Right to Financial Privacy Act (RFPA) governs the disclosure of financial records of individual bank customers to agencies of the federal government.

Once we receive your signed complaint, we will begin our review of the matter. Your complaint letter should be sent by FAX or U.S. Mail along with any attachments or supporting documentation.

Required information necessary to process your complaint or inquiry, if applicable:

Title 31 of the Code of Federal Regulations, Part 103, addresses the record keeping requirements of financial institutions. Under the provision of the regulation, financial institutions are required to retain records of any deposit in excess of $100 for a period of five years.

Furthermore, per the terms of your deposit agreement, you have a duty to notify the bank of any errors or unauthorized transfers from your account, with a certain numbers of days after the bank sends your statement. Typically, the timeframe is 45-60 days. If you did not notify the bank within the appropriate timeframe, the typically bank agreement will advised that you cannot make a claim against the bank related to unreported problems or unauthorized transactions.

I'm founding director and math coach for Edina Center for Academic Excellence (my "startup," actually a nonprofit organization), parent workshop director for Epsilon Camp, past president (current director) of the Minnesota Council for the Gifted and Talented (volunteer), and homeschooling father of four children (one now living independently and developing his career as a hacker in New York City's startup scene). I am very interested in research on mathematics education and education reform in general. I hope hackers come up with innovations that disrupt and improve primary, secondary, and higher education around the globe. Education policy is the issue that drew me to participate on Hacker News,

http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=4728123

and I'm glad to see that so many participants, from the founder on to the newest member, enjoy thinking about and checking facts on education issues.

Because I have worked the last several years as a teacher of voluntary, supplemental classes in prealgebra mathematics for advanced elementary-age learners, I have had the opportunity to review mathematics textbooks in the original English and Chinese and in English translation from China, Taiwan, many publishers in the United States, India, Canada, Singapore, Japan, and Russia. I have used those materials and many articles by mathematics education researchers to prepare class materials for the classes I teach. The parents of my students have come from India, China, Russia, Korea, Vietnam, Ghana, Haiti, Australia, Pakistan, Turkey, the Philippines, Romania, Poland, Somalia, and various parts of the United States. All of the parents are aware that United States schools don't meet a "world standard" in mathematics education, and look for something better for their children. I'd like to see every child everywhere have the opportunity to have the best possible primary education.

For good information to add to Hacker News discussions, I highly recommend the online bibliographies

"Intelligence Citations,"

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:WeijiBaikeBianji/IntelligenceCitations

and "Anthropology, Human Biology, and Race Citations,"

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:WeijiBaikeBianji/AnthropologyHumanBiologyRaceCitations

which lead to many reliable sources that would do much to elevate the discussion here. Another good place to look for information is the Wikipedia article "IQ classification,"

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/IQ_classification

one of the few reliable articles on a related topic yet posted to Wikipedia.

to HTML5 standards as part of celebrating the site's seventeenth birthday. or use the on-site comment form links, or the email links to the webmaster, or my postal address, to reach me with your thoughtful ideas on how to improve the site. Thanks for your kind--or blunt--suggestions. The suggestions I have already received are now in my to-do queue (but are crowded to low priority by work and parenting tasks). Yes, to be clear about that issue, I ("tokenadult" on HN and two other discussion sites) am the same person as Karl M. Bunday, the founder and webmaster of Learn in Freedom, and you may call me Karl in emails or in comments on Hacker News.

HIVEMIND RESPONSE NOTICE

The two biggest forms of hivemind that I encounter regularly on Hacker News are a knee-jerk reaction to decry the United States whenever world politics is discussed, and a completely credulous reaction to any claim of "mind over matter" in human medicine, no matter how poorly evidenced.

I do this at my own peril, but I try to rely on sources of information evidently not available to most Hacker News participants (or at least not regarded by many Hacker News participants) to point out that

1) the United States of America is certainly not a perfect country, but it is quite doubtful that the United States is the most harmful or blameworthy country in the world today,

and

2) "placebo medicine" has so far only been shown to have any effect at all on self-reported subjective patient symptoms such as pain and nausea that ebb and flow in the natural course of untreated disease.

If you have strong evidence that all of us can look at to check whether (for example) Russia is a greater force for good in the world than the United States, or that placebos can actually change any objectively measured physiological sign, please come forward with that evidence in your Hacker News comments. I will put up with silent downvotes any time people disagree with me, but I reserve the right to only be convinced by actual evidence from reliable sources.

You don't need my comments to help you see clearly, you have everything you already need in what I've written already. Joining those dots is up to you.

The main thing is, your life is up to you, blaming anyone else is just disempowering yourself. It doesn't work. Taking responsibility and choosing to create improvements for yourself does work.

Anything else is just substituting excuses to make yourself feel better, and just substituting an addiction to intoxicating narratives of zero responsibility, for instead of actually getting results.

You can start a company, no matter where you start from.

Oh, it looks hard from where you are? So give up when it looks hard from where you are and you'd rarely be successful anyway.

So persevere and your success is that much cooler, than if you'd peeled away a lesser risk.

The nature of risk, is that it's risky.

In a whole lot of ways it's easier when you have nothing. You're hungrier, more wily, more resourceful, you have less height to fall from. And more to gain. It's more immediate and important. When success and failure is the difference between your next meal, or a place to stay, you'll discover a depth of resourcefulness you didn't know you possessed.

If it's the difference between a Jag and a MacLaren, maybe you don't fight so hard.

So stop making excuses, and pretending you got to be privileged to make it. Buck up, if you want success.

counter narratives to the idea that you can't be an entrepreneurs unless are privileged - Make it work - do more with less - be scrappy - work smart - convert people into believers - convert believers into funders - ... or customers - if your Real Idea takes more than you have, make a Proxy idea to generate money so you can fund your real idea - stop complaining - stop blaming others - take responsibility - it's hard? it's in your mind. if anyone could do it, they would have. you wanted to be special, be a success? so earn it. - expecting success to just be given to you is acting privileged and entitled - it's not what you're given, it's what you choose to do with it that makes you count - risk comfort can be conditioned. so start practicing. - pretending their success is due to privilege is just trying to close the gap between you and them by diminishing your perception of them, instead of by making something that makes you more successful. this makes you feel good, and it doesn't work to get you results
